First-Year Engineering Overview
Core Subjects Covered:

✅ Mathematics: Calculus, Linear Algebra, Differential Equations.
✅ Physics: Mechanics, Thermodynamics, Waves & Optics.
✅ Chemistry: Engineering Chemistry, Material Science.
✅ Engineering Mechanics: Statics & Dynamics.
✅ Computer Programming: C, MATLAB (Basics).
✅ Electrical & Electronics: Circuit Analysis, Digital Logic.

Skills Gained:

✔ Strong foundation in mathematical and physical principles.
✔ Problem-solving and analytical thinking in engineering applications.
✔ Basic coding and computational skills for engineering solutions.
✔ Hands-on experience with AutoDesk tools for design and drafting.
✔ Teamwork and collaboration through lab work and projects.

Tools & Software Used:

MATLAB  (for numerical analysis)

AutoDesk

Projects / Lab Work:

Design Thinking for Social Innovation and Engineering Exploration.

Applied Physics Lab.

Basic circuit design and testing.

Coding algorithms for mathematical computations.


